column187: No comment...though I do like the final question :)
i suck at probability. but interesting questions.

They all seemed to be relatively easy questions to me but it also helps that I am a sports nut and 2 questions were sports related.  The weather one is iffy but Oregon is usually cooler than Pennsylvania.  I figure everyone knows the answer to the Atlantic vs Indian Oceans question.  The political one could go either way.  We don't know yet.  As for the crime rate one, I understand that it is based on a percentage, not an amount of crime.  I would be stunned if Columbus had a higher crime rate than Detroit.  just giving you my rationale with my answers.
Enjoyable study. I like to think I know all the answers but maybe I wasn't right for everyone.
Nay... feel a little dumb though. Regardless thanks for the survey. I had fun.
